headline: Why Analysts Think Colgate Could Be Fairly Valued As Its Growth Story Slowly Shifts
summary: Colgate-Palmolive’s latest valuation update leaves its fair value estimate essentially unchanged at about $87.21 per share, even as analysts recalibrate their near term expectations. The small shift in discount rate, alongside steady revenue growth assumptions, underscores a market narrative where short term execution risks are rising, but the longer term growth story is largely intact. Read on to see how you can track these subtle but important changes in the stock’s narrative going forward...
